(41, 13, 5, 51, 2, 8, 8, 'Take heed lest any man deceive you', 'Warning Against Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the need to be vigilant against deception. Mark warns to ''Take heed lest any man deceive you,'' while Colossians advises to ''Beware lest any man spoil you through philosophy and vain deceit.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
